-- Imam Mogamat Talaabodien (Ou Bappa) — full biography and timeline.
-- Run after 20250243. Source: family tree + A. Davids, "Mosques of the Bo-Kaap".
-- =============================================================================

UPDATE public.heritage_majlis
SET story_text = 'Imam Mogammad Talaabodien (1830–1922), known as Ou Bappa, Imam Taliep, Sheikh Mogammad Talab or Imam Talab. Born in Mauritius; died 1 July 1922 in Cape Town, aged 92. Son of Ebrahim Talaabodien and Ou Mama Talaabodien. First Imam of the second Indian mosque and Hanafi—the Quawwatul Islam Mosque, Loop Street, Bo-Kaap, Cape Town (A. Davids, "Mosques of the Bo-Kaap"). Fluent in Arabic and Urdu; studied in Mauritius and India. Husband of Moena, Moenouwara and Waseela Talaabodien; father of Imam Achmat (Bappa), Zobeida Essack, Gadija Talaabodien, Qaasiem, Fatima and many others. Patriarch of District Six and great-grandson of Tuan Guru; his legacy spans more than 80 grandchildren across the Taliep and Rakiep lines.'
WHERE ancestor_name = 'Imam Mogamat Talaabodien (Ou Bappa)';
